With Conda (Linux, Windows or Mac):

1. Clone this repository: git clone https://github.com/dEvasEnApati/pySIGEN.git
2. Create a new environment: conda create --name pySIGEN python=3.6 numpy pillow
3. Activate environment: source activate pySIGEN (Linux) or activate pySIGEN (Windows)
4. Install mono and other dependencies of SIGEN (see https://sites.google.com/site/sigenproject/downloads).
5. Install SIGEN from https://sites.google.com/site/sigenproject/downloads.
6. Modify the variables sigenMorphExtractor and sigenSmoothing in
<pySIGEN repository>/pySIGEN/executables to point to "MorphExtractorCL.exe" and "swcsmoothing.exe" respectively
7. Install pySIGEN: pip install <path to local pySIGEN repository>

Without Conda, with pip and virtualenvwrapper (only for Linux, Mac):

1. Clone this repository: git clone https://github.com/dEvasEnApati/pySIGEN.git
2. Create a new environment: mkvirtualenv pySIGEN
3. Activate environment: workon pySIGEN
4. Install mono and other dependencies of SIGEN (see https://sites.google.com/site/sigenproject/downloads)
5. Install SIGEN and its dependencies from https://sites.google.com/site/sigenproject/downloads.
6. Modify the variables sigenMorphExtractor and sigenSmoothing in
<pySIGEN repository>/pySIGEN/executables to point to "MorphExtractorCL.exe" and "swcsmoothing.exe" respectively
7. Install pySIGEN: pip install <path to local pySIGEN repository>


See file USAGE on how to use.